Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Brown meat in large skillet; drain. Return meat to skillet. Add tomatoes, water and seasoning mix; stir. Cook 10 minute, stirring occasionally. Stir in 1/4 cup sour cream. Place half the chips in 13x9-inch baking dish; cover with layers of half each of the meat mixture and cheese. Repeat layers. Bake 20 minute or until heated through. Top with onions and remaining sour cream.